\begin_layout Standard
The problems bank face is that an increased automation and machine learning
 could creates more hurdles in the task to setting up model risk controls
 (which themselves are use to evaluate many types of risk) across the investment
 banks rather difficult.
 The strategy for risk has typically followed a fragmented approach due
 to the varied goals of the business units within an investment bank (desks
 or divisions).
 A higher-level perspective of the overall risk is often based on adoption
 of a particular suite of models - which tend to vary across the banks.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The proposal attempts to evaluate how the notion of balancing risks across
 several business unit could may create avenues for taking risks unspecified
 risks - which the regulation may hardly control.
 By understanding this incentive quantitatively, one may be able to decide
 the cost-benefit analysis of ring-fencing and drawing up walls to discourage
 risk-taking and insider dealing.
 
\end_layout

