A necessary side-effect of such a separation is that absence of market for
 this overall risk.
 This becomes a rather structural problem since a large investment bank
 engages with varied (nearly all) sections of the industry.
 There is an issue of information asymmetry since since the clients who
 take long-term risk cannot be separated from those taking short-term risks
 except the banks.
