 profile at the bank is concerned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is hardly a problem since from the point of view of regulation - because
 it is indeed the very task of an investment bank to price the risk.
 As some of the industry is managed with corporate and M&A activities (e.g.
 by helping the clients participate in the market) or the clients may be
 asked mitigate their risks with financial products, clients necessarily
 end up possessing the risk that is implicitly known to the bank (which
 ends up finding our more about all clients than those outside the bank).
 Since it is up to the client to take her risks - banks only end up receiving
 a lot of information that they can't necessarily sell.
 This information a bias towards a decision in a Bayesian framework let's
 say is maintained at the bank.While strict controls over insider dealing
 may be implemented, there may be some information that mitigates the overall
 risk which is in common interest - since finding out about the overall
 risk is necessary for the surival of the bank.
\end_layout

