It is worth asserting that the models for subjective probability are fundamental
ly from how desks model the risk associated with securities - which is based
 on the market-microstucture (taking mean-reverting stochastic models for
 rates) and lognormal-like models for equity (in simple terms) and would
 have far more predictive power in the respecitve markets.
 Modeling such agents may be a difficult task but for the purposes of an
 aggregate consumer in the model, a lot of these uncertainties could be
 averaged out.
 The nature of risks - how they are communicated has only partly been.
